* Spectrum  = @{"archives.aros-exec.org/?function=showfile&file=emulation/computer/fuse-1.0.0.1.i386-aros.lha" system "OpenURL URL \"http://archives.aros-exec.org/?function=showfile&file=emulation/computer/fuse-1.0.0.1.i386-aros.lha\""}
* TADS      = @{"archives.aros-exec.org/?function=showfile&file=game/adventure/frobtads.i386-aros.rar" system "OpenURL URL \"http://archives.aros-exec.org/?function=showfile&file=game/adventure/frobtads.i386-aros.rar\""}

@{fg shadow}(I could not find any emulators for: Megazeux, AtariLynx, NeoGeo, or NES)@{fg text}

@{fg shadow}(I could not get emulators working for: Infocom, MegaDrive)@{fg text}

AROS note:  ZSNES does not work with eGame until you have run ZSNES once by itself & loaded a game ROM through ZSNES's own interface.


All OSes:  Due to limitations of the emulators, it is not possible to have launchers for OpenBOR, ScummVM, SDL_MAME & FPSE.


The eGame archive comes with a "useful_emulator_files" folder, which has:

* For both MorphOS & AROS, a "UAE" folder containing an optimal A500 config file, which the emulator will use if it is placed in it's folder.  But you must still supply a "rom.kick" file (A500 Kickstart image).  If you copy & rename a Kickstart ROM file from an AmigaForever CD, then ensure you also copy the "rom.key" file.

* For MorphOS, a "Hatari" folder containing a "tos.img" file needed by the emulator @{fg shadow}(missing from the MorphOS release for some reason)@{fg text}, and a "Data/.hatari.cfg" to replace the buggy one included in the MorphOS release of the emulator.

@endnode

@node "5_4" "Adding launcher commands to a tag"
@{fg fill}@{u}5.4. Adding launcher commands to a tag@{uu}@{fg text}
If you click on the Prefs button, you will get the Preferences window.  In the "Launchers" section you will see a list of all known Tags, and their associated launcher Commands.

To add commands to a tag, just double-click the tag @{fg shadow}(or you can click on the tag & then the "Edit Launch" button)@{fg text}.  This will open the "Edit a Launcher" window.

From here you can type directly in the "Commands" text box, which you can think of as a list of Shell commands that eGame should execute for each game. You might write something like the following line:
  CD Sys:C
  RunInDOSBox "%g" %p

The alternative to typing this manually would be to click on the "Add program" button.  This would open a file requester for picking a program.  If you chose the RunInDOSBox program, then you would see it add these lines:
  CD "${AppDir/RunInDOSBox}"
  RunInDOSBox "%g" %p

I'll explain that CD AppDir line later.  For now imagine that you double-clicked on the MS-DOS game Frontier (which has the path "Work:games/Frontier.exe"). This would cause eGame to execute the following Shell commands:
  CD Sys:C
  RunInDOSBox "Work:games/Frontier.exe" 

In other words %g gets replaced by the path of the game you double-clicked on. So what does %p do?  When you Edit a game, at the bottom of a window you should notice a "Launch parameters" box.  Let's say you put "WINDOW" in there for the Frontier game.  Now when you run that particular game, eGame will execute the following Shell commands:
  CD Sys:C
  RunInDOSBox "Work:games/Frontier.exe" WINDOW

This allows you to customise how each game is launched, in case it needs any special settings.


So what was that CD AppDir line we saw earlier?  Here it is again:
  CD "${AppDir/RunInDOSBox}"

This is an AmigaOS4.1 feature which I simulate on other OSes.  Every program (in this case RunInDOSBox) has an environmental variable which says where the program can be found.  This is really handy, as it means it is possible for the same script to work on different people's machines.  And if the game is not yet known, then eGame is clever enough to ask you where to find it.

Let's say that RunInDOSBox is known to be installed in Sys:C .  Then the earlier line will be automatically expanded to this:
  CD "Sys:C"


You can of course edit any existing launchers too!

If you have trouble getting a launcher to work, then I suggest enabling the option "Show shell output of launcher".  This allows you to see error messages.


@endnode

@node "6_0" "DonationShareware registration (to get rid of the 10 game limitation)"
@{fg fill}@{u}6. DonationShareware registration (to get rid of the 10 game limitation)@{uu}@{fg text}
@{b}Please read this carefully!@{ub}

1.  The eGame demo is fully functional, apart from only showing up to 10 games. So please test eGame to be sure it meets your needs & works well on your computer.

2.  After donating, I will send you a personalised key file.  This unlocks eGame, meaning it will show all games added to it.  Donating does not @{u}guarantee@{uu} that I will add new features you want, nor fix problems you have...  so if you really need something added or fixed, then @{u}email me@{uu} & please do not donate @{u}until after@{uu} I have improved eGame to your satisfaction.

The key file will of course work with all future versions of eGame.

3.  To donate, please go to the following web page & click on the Donate button:

@{"cshandley.co.uk/email/" system "OpenURL URL \"http://cshandley.co.uk/email/\""}

This should take you to PayPal's web site, and allow you to donate to me (Chris Handley), using either a debit/credit card or your own PayPal account.

The minimum donation is 2 Pounds, but if you think eGame is worth more than that, then I encourage you to donate what you think it is worth. :-)

@{u}Make sure you click on "Add special instructions to the seller"@{uu}, and then in the box that appears:
* Write "For eGame."
* Write the name of your main OS @{fg shadow}(AmigaOS4, AROS or MorphOS)@{fg text}.

@{fg shadow}(The key file will work on all OSes, but knowing which OS will help me decide whether to release new programs for your OS.)@{fg text}

4.  PayPal will supply me with your name & email address.  I will use both when creating a personalised key file, which I will then email you.  You need to put the "eGame.key" file in eGame's folder.  While I will try to send your key file within 24 hours, please allow up to a week (in case I am very busy or on holiday).

The key file is for your use only, and of course must never be given to anyone else.


@endnode

@node "7_0" "Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)"
@{fg fill}@{u}7. Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)@{uu}@{fg text}
@{"7.1. What on earth is 'DonationShareware'?!?" link "7_1"}
@{"7.2. eGame fails to start some games" link "7_2"}
@{"7.3. Isn't eGame's NAME rather similar to the 68k program iGame?  And the Windows program AmiGame?" link "7_3"}
@{"7.4. Could you release eGame for 68k Amigas?" link "7_4"}
@endnode

@node "7_1" "What on earth is 'DonationShareware'?!?"
@{fg fill}@{u}7.1. What on earth is 'DonationShareware'?!?@{uu}@{fg text}
It's my name for a cross between Donationware & Shareware!  It is Donationware in the sense that I ask you to donate what you think it's worth (above a pretty low minimum).  It is Shareware in the sense that it's not quite fully functional (until registered).

But if you can think of a better name, then let me know!

@endnode

@node "7_2" "eGame fails to start some games"
@{fg fill}@{u}7.2. eGame fails to start some games@{uu}@{fg text}
@{b}If you are using AmigaOS4@{ub}, then this is probably due to an OS4 bug (in WbRun).  Using Workbench, select the game's icon, and then choose "Icons > Information..." from Workbench's menu.  This should open a window.  Change to the Icon tab, and if "Start from:" is set to "Shell", then please change it to "Workbench".  Finally click Save.  Now try running the game again using eGame.

If this is not the case, or doesn't solve your problem, then please contact me.

@endnode

@node "7_3" "Isn't eGame's NAME rather similar to the 68k program iGame?  And the Windows program AmiGame?"
@{fg fill}@{u}7.3. Isn't eGame's NAME rather similar to the 68k program iGame?  And the Windows program AmiGame?@{uu}@{fg text}
Yes, but it's actually quite hard to come-up with a completely novel name that is short & still hints at what it does.  The fact that there were already (at least!) two programs (with names ending in -Game) should prove that.  Plus I'm completely useless at thinking of names (just look at my earlier programs!).

@endnode

@node "7_4" "Could you release eGame for 68k Amigas?"
@{fg fill}@{u}7.4. Could you release eGame for 68k Amigas?@{uu}@{fg text}
Very likely, if there is interest.  Email me!


@endnode

@node "8_0" "Contact details"
@{fg fill}@{u}8. Contact details@{uu}@{fg text}
If you have any problems with eGame, then let me know!  You can contact me by email, using the address given on this web page:

@{"cshandley.co.uk/email" system "OpenURL URL \"http://cshandley.co.uk/email\""}

If for some reason you cannot email me, then I can be found on AmigaWorld.net & www.Amigans.net as "ChrisH".  I suggest you PM me on AmigaWorld.net, as I may not notice forum posts (nor PMs on Amigans.net!).


@endnode

@node "9_0" "The future"
@{fg fill}@{u}9. The future@{uu}@{fg text}
Here is a list of POSSIBLE thing that I might add:

* A little window for AROS users to drop games onto (instead of having to use a file requester).  @{i}But only if AROS users feel the need for this.@{ui}

If you are interested in any of these ideas, or have any suggestions of your own, then feel free to email me!  Your input may help me decided what to do next.


@endnode

@node "10_0" "Thanks"
@{fg fill}@{u}10. Thanks@{uu}@{fg text}
In chronological order, thanks to:
* Martin 'mason' Merz, since I use some of his AISS icons for eGame's 'toolbar'.
* Joel Edberg, for suggesting the idea of a game launcher, as well as testing & additional ideas.
* Itix & Piru for hints on how to load icon images on MorphOS.

Sorry if I missed anyone.


@endnode

@node "11_0" "History"
@{fg fill}@{u}11. History@{uu}@{fg text}
r5 (05.02.2013)
* You can now create Launchers for games with particular tags (see the new Preferences window).
* Comes with predefined Launchers for many emulators.
* Automatically tags many many types of emulated game files (e.g. Roms, Disks, Tapes).
* Dropping a folder now finds & adds many types of emulated game files (see above).
* Launchers can use game-specific parameters (set in the "Edit game" window).
* Added a prefs option to exit eGame after a game has been launched.  Requested by Helge.
* Added a prefs option to show shell output of launchers.

* Added a button to open the game's folder.  Requested by a user.
* Fixed editing of multiple entries only editing half of them.
* The OK button in the "Edit game" window now respond to the Enter key.  Thanks to a tip from Antonio.
* The "Tag All" window now unselects tags after they have been used.
* No-longer tags Zip files as Floppy (disks).
* Fixed illegal memory reads when checking the file extension of very short filenames.
* The installer now warns you if you don't have TextEditor installed.
* The eGame logo is now less garish!

r4 (17.01.2013)
* MorphOS; Removed warnings about the MorphOS version, as I fixed my Efika & so am able to test eGame on MOS :-) .
* MorphOS; PNG icons are now shown :-) @{fg shadow}(and 4-colour classic icons too)@{fg text}.
* MorphOS; Fixed the installer not working.
* MorphOS; Really fixed the Amiga version string this time!
* AmigaOS4; Worked-around OS bugs that made scaled icons look bad (or not visible at all on 16-bit screens).
* The installer now warns you if you don't have NList installed.
* eGame now reports if it failed to start because NList was missing.
* Icons are not enlarged beyond x2 @{fg shadow}(let me know if you think they still look ugly!)@{fg text}.

r3 (07.01.2013)
* Now comes with an installer, to avoid users accidentally deleting their eGame.list & eGame.key files.
* Added support for screenshots to be shown @{fg shadow}(instead of icons)@{fg text}.  Requested by several people!
* Now enlarges small icons @{fg shadow}(but only by integer amounts, like x2, x3, etc)@{fg text}.
  Please let me know if you dislike OR like this!
* Add a "Last played" column.  Requested by someone @{fg shadow}(not sure who though!)@{fg text}.
* Added "Favourite" as a built-in tag.
* For "Play count" it now shows nothing @{fg shadow}(instead of 0)@{fg text}, if you have never played the game.
* Now handles multiple files dropped at the same time.  Requested by Helge.
* No-longer uses the WbRun command @{fg shadow}(nor the Open command on AROS)@{fg text}.

r2 (29.12.2012)
* Moved the Icon & "Filter tag" windows into the main window, due to user demand.  @{fg shadow}(It's taken some time to convince me, but it does look better!)@{fg text}
* Added a "Play count" column.  Requested by someone @{fg shadow}(not sure who though!)@{fg text}.
* Tries to fix tags which were wrongly entered by the user.  Spaces & slashes are now treated as commas.
* Now reports if your key file is corrupt (rather than just ignoring it).
* Fixed some games failing to start on AmigaOS4 @{fg shadow}(or even crashing)@{fg text}, by working-around a WbRun bug.  Reported by Tommysammy & RibDevil.
* Fixed a changed Tags box being ignored if you clicked on a button (like OK) without first pressing Enter.
* Fixed editing of game tags not immediately affecting whether those games are filtered.
* Fixed scrollbars not being exactly aligned with their list.  Reported by Krashan.
* Fixed Amiga version string to be legal.  Problem spotted by Krashan.

r1 (27.12.2012)
* First public release. 
@endnode
